1
00:00:00,230 --> 00:00:07,010
In this video, we are going to see an example of gRPC usage in microservice communications.

2
00:00:07,220 --> 00:00:08,420
Think about that.

3
00:00:08,420 --> 00:00:16,460
We have a shopping cart microservices that expose ad item into shopping cart RESTful http API to the

4
00:00:16,460 --> 00:00:17,630
client application.

5
00:00:18,440 --> 00:00:19,400
This shopping cart.

6
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:26,360
Microservices receives a single request from a client and dispatch it to various microservices.

7
00:00:26,630 --> 00:00:31,910
Aggregate the results and send them back to the requesting client application.

8
00:00:32,630 --> 00:00:39,140
Such operations typically require synchronous communication as to produce an immediate response.

9
00:00:39,620 --> 00:00:47,060
In this example, backend calls from the shopping cart microservices are performed using the gRPC.

10
00:00:47,510 --> 00:00:52,100
gRPC communication requires both client and server components.

11
00:00:52,280 --> 00:00:57,440
You can see the image that shopping cart microservices implements gRPC client.

12
00:00:58,130 --> 00:01:03,290
The client makes synchronous gRPC call to the backend microservices.

13
00:01:03,320 --> 00:01:07,820
This backend microservices are implemented as a gRPC server.

14
00:01:08,330 --> 00:01:13,820
In our case, backend microservices are product and discount microservices.

15
00:01:14,090 --> 00:01:21,380
Shopping cart refers to product detail information and also latest discount information before adding

16
00:01:21,380 --> 00:01:22,460
item into cart.

17
00:01:22,940 --> 00:01:31,160
As you can see that the gRPC endpoints must be configured for the Http two protocol that is required

18
00:01:31,160 --> 00:01:33,050
for the gRPC communication.

19
00:01:33,620 --> 00:01:40,160
In microservices world, most of the communication uses asynchronous communication patterns, but some

20
00:01:40,160 --> 00:01:44,000
operations require direct calls for the immediate response.

21
00:01:44,030 --> 00:01:50,270
gRPC should be the primary choice for direct synchronous communication between backend microservices.

22
00:01:50,270 --> 00:01:57,470
It is high performance communication protocol based on Http two, and protocol buffers make it a perfect

23
00:01:57,470 --> 00:01:58,040
choice.

